<img class="wp-image-1308310" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/NSITF.jpg?resize=500%2C389&#038;ssl=1" alt="Buhari commends insurance sector on free cover for health workers" width="500" height="389" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/NSITF.jpg?resize=300%2C233&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/NSITF.jpg?resize=58%2C45&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/NSITF.jpg?resize=249%2C194&amp;ssl=1 249w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/NSITF.jpg?resize=167%2C130&amp;ssl=1 167w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/NSITF.jpg?w=450&amp;ssl=1 450w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> President Muhammad Buhari has commended the insurance sector for supporting the government with free insurance cover for frontline health workers. He gave the commendation during his nationwide broadcast on Monday. He said: “In keeping with our government’s promise to improve the welfare of healthcare workers, we have signed a memorandum of understanding on the provision of hazard allowances and other incentives with key health sector professional associations. “We have also procured insurance cover for 5,000 frontline health workers. ALSO READ: COVID-19: Twelve health workers test positive in Sokoto “At this point, I must commend the insurance sector for their support in achieving this within a short period of time.” Meanwhile, the insurance sector is excited that their effort is being appreciated at the highest level of authority, Buhari. Chairman, Nigeria Insurers Association, NIA, Mr. Tope Smart, said they are happy that for the first time, their role is being appreciated. He stated that the recognition will further spur them to do more. According to Smart, the insurance sector had always played major roles in the economy, but this is the first time they are getting a presidential recognition. He said they looked forward to more partnership with the Federal Government in developing the country. Vanguard It is welcome development, but... — NMA, NARD & PSN Unacceptable to us — Lab scientists Disparity is only snag — NUAP By Chioma Obinna Reactions have continued to trail the life insurance provided by the Federal Government and the Nigerian insurance industry for 5,000 frontline health workers in the… April 28, 2020 In "Health" Nigerians have continued to hail President Muhammadu Buhari on the Federal Government’s welfare package  for health workers as Nigeria continues to fight COVID-19. April 29, 2020 In "News" Olasunkanmi Akoni A consortium of six insurance companies in Nigeria on Saturday put together an insurance cover of N5billion for health workers and volunteers tackling the coronavirus pandemic in the state. The firms are - Leadway Assurance Company Limited, Custodian and Allied Insurance Plc, Lasaco Assurance Plc, AIICO Insurance Plc,… April 4, 2020 In "News"